Interpretation

"The tokens correspond to common Hindi postpositions and case markers, such as \"के\", \"की\", \"का\", \"को\", \"में\", and \"की\", which attach to nouns and pronouns to indicate grammatical relationships like possession, location, and object marking. These markers are highly frequent and essential for sentence structure in Hindi."
